name: Susan G Taylor CRNA Corp - COVID Vaccine CLinic
info: Join us for a free vaccine clinic on Saturday June 12th from Noon-2pm at Kulshan Brewing Company (K2- 1538 Kentucky Street)! Walk-ins are welcome for the Moderna first and second doses. As a part of the statewide Pints for Pokes initiative, Kulshan will be offering a beer on the house for any person who gets vaccinated on Saturday, and any person who has been vaccinated in the past month (May 15th through end of June). Folks getting vaccinated on Saturday will also be entered into the "Shot of a Lifetime” Million Dollar Washington State Lottery Drawing.

name: Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine - COVID Vaccine Clinic
address: 1750 112th Avenue Northeast, STE C-102, Bellevue WA, 98004
info: ***We provide MODERNA 1st and 2nd doses*** Please sign up for an appointment time. When you arrive to the clinic, please continue to wear your face covering, practice physical distancing and wash your hands frequently to help reduce transmission. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay for 15 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Due to the limited supplies of vaccines provided to us each week, we are unable to take walk-ins, so please make an appointment. ***Directions to the Hawker Center for Integrative Medicine:*** Our clinic is located in the Hidden Valley Office Complex. 1) When you arrive at the complex, take either driveway all the way to the back of the building. 2) We are located on the prominent corner at the very back of the building and we have our own private entrance. Look for the parking lot with the number "2" in a big steel frame. Do NOT go into the main building for we have a private entrance accessible directly from the parking lot. Look for our sign with our logo in the window and a door with the number "C-102" on it, visible from the parking lot. ***Visit our website for further contact information and directions to the clinic: https://www.hawkerhealth.com/contact-us/ ***
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Yakima County Health District COVID Vaccination Site
info:
Additional Information: ***1ST & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS!!!!*** The
vaccination clinic will take place at Bale Breaker Brewing. This clinic will be
outside. Masks are required. Please wear clothing which allows access to your
shoulder. All individuals 12 and over are eligible to get vaccinated. Those under 18
must be accompanied by a parent/guardian or must get parental consent via
video/phone call or paper format.

Informacion Adicional: ***VACUNAS DE PRIMERA Y SEGUNDA DOSIS PFIZER!!!***
La clínica de vacunación se ubicara en Bale Breaker Brewing. Se requieren
máscaras. Por favor, use ropa que permita acceso a su brazo. Todas las personas
mayores de 12 años son elegibles para vacunarse. Los menores de 18 años deben
estar acompañados por un padre/tutor o deben obtener el consentimiento de los
padres por video/llamada telefónica o en papel.

info: This is a Johnson & Johnson mobile clinic being held at Capital Mall, 625 Black Lake Blvd SW, Olympia WA, 98502 for anyone age 18 and older.  We will be located in the Sephora parking lot between Red Robin and the Cinemark movie theatre. Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers, if needed. • Please arrive at your scheduled appointment time. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
